macro.title: Data, not doom: Gary Keller makes the case for housing optimism
macro.what: Keller Williams forecasts 4.3 million home sales, $2.4 trillion in volume, and 5.9% mortgage rates for 2026.
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.
